# Collector Notes

Promtail is the pedagogical collector model for v0.12.0.

## What A Collector Does

A log collector runs in the cluster, reads pod container logs written to stdout and stderr, attaches Kubernetes metadata, and sends the log streams to Loki.

## Manual Prerequisites

Promtail or Alloy must be installed and configured manually if you want real log collection. `k8s-forge` does not generate installation manifests, package manager commands, credentials, or secrets.

## Labels

The generated Kubernetes resources use labels such as:

```text
app={{ app.name }}
app.kubernetes.io/name={{ app.name }}
```

A collector may expose these labels as `app`, `app_kubernetes_io_name`, or another relabeled form. Adjust LogQL selectors after checking the labels available in Grafana Explore.

## Application Logging

The application should write meaningful logs to stdout and stderr. Structured JSON logs are useful, but v0.12.0 does not require or generate an application logging format.

## Future Direction

Alloy can be used in future versions as a broader telemetry collector. v0.12.0 keeps the output limited to readiness notes and local examples.
